Dear contributors dear <@1352785241252565174>. In my onboarding today I discussed with Oscar on which KPIs we will manage the community and to ensure progress in creating something valuable. I just want to share my thoughts and I am happy to learn what you think about this. Draft: 

To help us steer this amazing GenAI community as it grows, Iâ€™d like to suggest a lightweight but powerful KPI system. Itâ€™s designed to balance long-term vision with day-to-day insights:

Top-Level KPIs (big picture)

Member Growth & Reach â€“ Are we growing globally + inclusively?

Engagement Rate â€“ How many members actively participate?

Innovation Output â€“ Are we co-creating GenAI knowledge and projects?

Influence Score â€“ Are we making waves outside the community?

Mid-Level KPIs (community health)

Activation Rate â€“ Do new members engage in their first week?

Contributor % â€“ Are we enabling broad participation?

Response Time â€“ Are questions + ideas being picked up fast?

Retention â€“ Are members staying and returning?

Ops-Level KPIs (daily signals)

Post-to-Comment Ratio â€“ Are we sparking real dialogue?

Event Attendance vs. Sign-ups â€“ Are sessions landing well?

Moderation Flags â€“ Is the space safe and respectful?

Cross-Channel Activity â€“ Are members engaging across Discord, GitHub, etc.?

This system gives us clarity and flexibilityâ€”and helps us keep this space meaningful, global, and aligned with the GenAI mission.

Happy to co-create this furtherâ€”open to feedback, iterations, or starting a mini-pilot together if it this will help.

Hi <@1359552583244583153> and @everyone. Sesh is integrated across our server and it does have polling / surveying capabilities, so I would suggest you use it for the purpose. 
You can use the poll functionality in Sesh Discord bot to conduct surveys. You can create text-based questions with multiple options, allowing users to vote on them. Additionally, it offers features that make it suitable for surveys, such as:
- Allowing users to add their own answers to the poll
- Anonymous voting, which can be useful for honest survey responses.
- Live-updating results with bar graphs, giving real-time feedback on survey outcomes.
You can create these polls via slash commands or the web dashboard. 
It is robust enough to be used for general surveys and community feedback collection within our discord server.
